<subSubSection pageId="806" pageNumber="807" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="806" pageNumber="807">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="806" pageNumber="807">
This subspecies is known from southern California (Fall 1901a: 48; Mateu 1974: 264), 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Nevada”">&quot;Nevada&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Horn 1882: 134), southeastern Colorado (Bent County, CNC), and central Texas (Casey 1920: 270). The records from northeastern Kansas (Popenoe 1877: 23) and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Oregon”">&quot;Oregon&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Horn 1882: 134) need confirmation. The previous records from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Colorado”">&quot;Colorado&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Wickham 1902: 239; Mateu 1974: 264) were probably based on a misinterpretation of the type locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
